BT /F2 10 Tf 54 686 Td (Displayed field: Total Properties) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 662 Td (  - Formula: `count\(properties owned by current user\)`) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 650 Td (  - Source: `dashboard/views.py:index`) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 638 Td (  - Explanation: Counts the landlord/admin user's properties.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 626 Td (  - Example: If the user owns Green Court and Blue Court, total properties = `2`.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 54 606 Td (Displayed field: Total Tenants) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 582 Td (  - Formula: `count\(tenants where tenant.unit.property.user == current user\)`) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 570 Td (  - Source: `dashboard/views.py:index`) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 558 Td (  - Explanation: Counts tenants attached to units in the user's properties.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 546 Td (  - Example: If Green Court has 6 tenants and Blue Court has 4 tenants, total tenants = `6 +) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 534 Td (    4 = 10`.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 54 514 Td (Displayed field: Total Units) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 490 Td (  - Formula: `sum\(Property.total_units for current user's properties\)`) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 478 Td (  - Source: `dashboard/views.py:index`) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 466 Td (  - Explanation: Uses the declared total unit count stored on each property.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 454 Td (  - Example: Green Court total units = 20, Blue Court total units = 12, total units = `20 +) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 442 Td (    12 = 32`.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 54 422 Td (Displayed field: Recent Property Occupancy) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 398 Td (  - Formula: `occupied_units = count\(property.units where status == "occupied"\)`) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 386 Td (  - Source: `dashboard/views.py:index`) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 374 Td (  - Explanation: Shows occupied units for each recent property.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 362 Td (  - Example: If a property has 12 units and 9 are marked occupied, display = `9/12 units) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 350 Td (    occupied`.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 54 330 Td (Displayed field: Monthly Revenue) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 306 Td (  - Formula: `sum\(Payment.amount where payment.user == current user and payment.date >=) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 294 Td (    today - 30 days\)`) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 282 Td (  - Source: `dashboard/views.py:index`) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 270 Td (  - Explanation: Adds all payments received in the last 30 days.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 258 Td (  - Example: Payments in last 30 days are KES 8,000, KES 12,000, and KES 5,000. Monthly) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 246 Td (    revenue = `8,000 + 12,000 + 5,000 = 25,000`.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 54 226 Td (Displayed field: Previous-Month Revenue) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 202 Td (  - Formula: `sum\(Payment.amount where today - 60 days <= payment.date < today - 30 days\)`) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 190 Td (  - Source: `dashboard/views.py:index`) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 178 Td (  - Explanation: Adds payments from the previous 30-day window for comparison.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 166 Td (  - Example: Payments in the previous window are KES 9,000 and KES 6,000. Previous-month) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 154 Td (    revenue = `9,000 + 6,000 = 15,000`.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 54 134 Td (Displayed field: Revenue Increase Percentage) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 110 Td (  - Formula: `\(\(monthly_revenue - previous_month_revenue\) / previous_month_revenue\) * 100`,) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 98 Td (    rounded to 1 decimal place. If previous-month revenue is zero, the percentage is `0`.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 86 Td (  - Source: `dashboard/views.py:index`) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 74 Td (  - Explanation: Measures the percentage change between the current 30-day revenue and the) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 54 62 Td (    previous 30-day revenue.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 54 30 Td (Page 2 of 16) Tj ET
endstream
